ilog in to the management panel with the above username and password.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iModifying Open5GS Configuration Files		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAfter Open5GS is installed, you will need to modify the configuration		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifiles to match the parameters of our CBRS LTE network. We only need to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imake the following changes:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Change MCC/MNC from the default 999/70 to CBRS's 315/010.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iSimply search globally for `mcc: 999` and `mnc: 70`, and replace them		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwith `mcc: 315` and `mnc: 010` respectively:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Make the MME component listen on `eth0` (or your actual network card		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iname) interface instead of `127.0.0.2`, otherwise the base station		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icannot connect to the core network.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
