i`acs.freedomfi.com`, a TR-069 server, to automatically obtain		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iconfigurations. Although this remote management server was shut down		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwhen Helium Mobile discontinued its CBRS network, our base station		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwill still continuously try to connect to this server. When using		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iMagma to build the core network, since the Magma core network itself		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ihas TR-069 server functionality, we can keep remote management enabled		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iand simply hijack remote management requests to our TR-069 server.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
